<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747149>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Cheethamia howei Shaw. (a) holotype, LSUMG-I 8237; Cretaceous, Campanian, Saratoga Chalk, Howard County, Arkansas, USA. (b–f) NHMUK BZ 4809; Cretaceous, Maastrichtian, Lake Ridge Apartments, Livingston, Alabama, USA; (b) ovicellate and non-ovicellate autozooids and an avicularium; (c) opesia of non-ovicellate autozooid showing occlusor lamina and a pair of closely spaced oral spine bases; (d) ovicellate autozooid with transverse wall visible in opesia; (e) avicularium; (f) ancestrula (lower centre) and first-budded autozooids. Scale bars: a, b, e, f = 500 µm; c = 100 µm; d = 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747149/files/figure.png" .

